data.name: label2.Text
data.value: Get on your mat with your legs extended behind the upper body. Push your hands to the ground alongside your stomach and tuck your toes into the ground. Press your elbows against your ribs, making sure your fingers are pointing forward toward your head. The hands and toes must entirely support your body weight. Squeeze your thighs and tighten your abdominal muscles to remain in a straight line, then slowly push up and down. You should feel your entire body weight moving in the shoulders and chest.
